1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,712
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,795 --> 00:00:06,840
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,717 --> 00:00:10,760
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:13,012
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

6
00:00:17,225 --> 00:00:18,309
[Atoy] <i>I've located the father and child.</i>

7
00:00:18,393 --> 00:00:20,145
This is my wish, Papa!

8
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:22,272
[Sabrina] <i>That we go to this theme park!</i>

9
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:24,357
[Ibyang] <i>Janine! You came too?</i>

10
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:25,817
You're all alone now, Ibyang.

11
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,152
PREVIOUSLY

12
00:00:27,235 --> 00:00:29,821
[Janine] <i>I found my real mommy.</i>

13
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,156
<i>Where's your fake dad?</i>

14
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:33,074
Someone is bullying you at school?

15
00:00:33,158 --> 00:00:34,951
She teases me for being adopted.

16
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:36,661
And now, this.

17
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:38,496
I'm the new trainee here.

18
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:41,082
[Atoy] <i>Do you want me to cover for you?</i>

19
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:42,333
<i>I'll stand in for you.</i>

20
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:44,753
- [growls]
- [screams]

21
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:46,337
[Noel] <i>You're not supposed</i>
<i>to touch guests here!</i>

22
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,338
<i>Isn't my child already traumatized?!</i>

23
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:48,840
- [grunts]
- [swooshes]

24
00:00:48,923 --> 00:00:51,092
[Noel] <i>I just want to be with my child.</i>

25
00:00:51,176 --> 00:00:53,470
<i>My wife left me for another man,</i>

26
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:55,096
<i>because she wanted someone richer.</i>

27
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,600
[Maxwell] <i>How can we build</i>
<i>our family if your child is here?</i>

28
00:00:58,683 --> 00:01:00,143
Of course you'll waste
all your time on her.

29
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:02,687
[Maxwell, in English] <i>Either</i>
<i>boarding school or we leave her here.</i>

30
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,606
[Janine] <i>You know, if your mother</i>
<i>is looking for you,</i>

31
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:06,733
<i>maybe you'd be wearing nicer clothes now.</i>

32
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:07,776
<i>Like me.</i>

33
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:11,237
But how would she look for you
if she doesn't love you?

34
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:12,405
[Janine cackles]

35
00:01:12,489 --> 00:01:13,448
[Mercado] <i>Where are you going?</i>

36
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,533
[Atoy] <i>I just have a promise to fulfill.</i>

37
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:16,659
Ibyang.

38
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:18,244
Psst, hey.

39
00:01:18,328 --> 00:01:19,829
Why are you sulking there?

40
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:25,668
- [sobs]
- Oh?

41
00:01:27,003 --> 00:01:29,047
[sobbing]

42
00:01:30,715 --> 00:01:31,591
Why?

43
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:35,094
[sobbing]

44
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:39,098
- Huh?
- [sobbing]

45
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:42,560
Why? What happened to you? Huh?

46
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,479
[music fades]

47
00:01:44,562 --> 00:01:45,563
Psst, hey.

48
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:46,648
[Atoy] What happened here?

49
00:01:46,731 --> 00:01:48,441
Why is she crying? What did you do?

50
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:50,110
Nothing!

51
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:52,237
We… We didn't do anything.

52
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,447
We were even joking around,

53
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:56,866
doing magic tricks to cheer her up.

54
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,201
We didn't do anything.

55
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:00,495
She was already sad earlier.

56
00:02:01,704 --> 00:02:04,624
Well, it's obvious why, isn't it?

57
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:07,961
[gentle music playing]

58
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:09,712
All right, I'll take care of her.

59
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:11,965
- All right then.
- Hmm, thanks.

60
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,508
Now let's enjoy. Come on!

61
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:14,926
- Psst, let it go.
- [Tonet mutters]

62
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:16,970
- Don't fuss about it.
- Teddy, are you okay?

63
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,848
Psst! Wifey!

64
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,641
[Atoy] What's happening to you, huh?

65
00:02:24,519 --> 00:02:27,230
Why are you here, Master?

66
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:30,191
I thought you had work?

67
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:32,777
Oh, I finished my work,

68
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:35,321
so I could join you here.

69
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:41,244
[sighs] I'm sorry.

70
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:47,000
I know I promised to be with you, but…

71
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:50,587
I prioritized my work
because I really had to do it.

72
00:02:51,629 --> 00:02:52,922
But now I'm here.

73
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:55,508
[smirks]

74
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:58,219
So, what really happened?

75
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:00,263
Why are you crying?

76
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:06,936
Is it true my mother doesn't love me?

77
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,606
[melancholic music playing]

78
00:03:10,607 --> 00:03:12,150
Who told you that?

79
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:17,739
If she did love me,

80
00:03:18,907 --> 00:03:20,992
why did she give me up for adoption?

81
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:26,039
So, she's probably not looking for me.

82
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:32,378
[music fades]

83
00:03:32,462 --> 00:03:34,923
[suave theme music playing]

84
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:04,994
- Gavin, have you found Janine's teacher?
- [indistinct]

85
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,080
<i>I am so happy, because…</i>

86
00:04:07,163 --> 00:04:08,122
Gavin?

87
00:04:08,206 --> 00:04:09,040
Oh.

88
00:04:09,123 --> 00:04:10,041
What is it, Auntie?

89
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,292
What are we going to do?

90
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:14,087
You're always on your phone.
You don't listen.

91
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:17,298
I said we need to find Janine's teacher,

92
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:19,884
so I can talk to the one bullying her.

93
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:22,178
Isn't that just kids quarreling, Auntie?

94
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,596
Let's not interfere.

95
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:28,059
[in English] Bullying
is a serious problem, Gavin.

96
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:30,228
<i>I hope they don't run</i>
<i>out of chocolate for us.</i>

97
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,855
Ah, Auntie, can I wander around first?

98
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,065
[in English] Okay, fine.

99
00:04:34,148 --> 00:04:35,191
Go, have fun.

100
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,901
- [Audrey] I'll handle this.
- Thank you, Auntie!

101
00:04:37,568 --> 00:04:39,612
- [pensive music playing]
- [Cathy laughs on video]

102
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,784
[in English] Let's go look
for your teacher, dear.

103
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:48,913
[music fades]

104
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:50,999
Why are you thinking
about that now, Ibyang?

105
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:55,086
That's what Janine told me.

106
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:59,799
She said she found her real mother,

107
00:04:59,882 --> 00:05:02,218
because her mom looked for her.

108
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:05,346
[melancholic music playing]

109
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,018
Sometimes, Ibyang…

110
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:13,104
there are parents who really

111
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:15,940
can't raise their children.

112
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:19,902
That's why they give them up for adoption.

113
00:05:22,613 --> 00:05:23,823
But, of course…

114
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,745
I don't know

115
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,873
what your parents' intentions were

116
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:33,875
when they did that to you.

117
00:05:34,375 --> 00:05:40,089
Maybe they're hoping
that if you go to another family,

118
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:43,801
you'll have a better life.

119
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:45,636
That's tough.

120
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,430
I'm not saying it's right or wrong,

121
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:50,600
but of course, they each have
their own reasons.

122
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:55,730
Parents have different reasons
for doing that,

123
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:58,858
and I don't know the answer.

124
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,698
But what Janine did, what she told you?

125
00:06:06,949 --> 00:06:09,452
I don't like that. It's wrong.

126
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:12,288
She shouldn't have said that to you.

127
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:16,167
I thought that child had changed,
so I let it pass.

128
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,294
[music fades]

129
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,462
But not anymore.

130
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:20,922
[dramatic sting]

131
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:23,382
Come on.

132
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:25,218
Where are we going?

133
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,387
I'll talk to the mother she's so proud of.

134
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:30,473
[light music playing]

135
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:33,684
Let's go.

136
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:37,188
They're really enjoying it here so much!

137
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,982
- What flavor do you want?
- [child 1] Chocolate.

138
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,275
[Cathy] Chocolate too?

139
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:43,694
- Mine too, chocolate.
- Chocolate also? You?

140
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:44,987
[children] Chocolate.

141
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,532
Chocolate! Wow, chocolate is really

142
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:48,741
- their favorite!
- [Atoy] Excuse me.

143
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,535
[Cathy] Oh, them too.

144
00:06:50,618 --> 00:06:52,078
- Do you want ice cream?
- [Cathy exclaims gleefully]

145
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,579
- Yes, please.
- [Cathy] Chocolate.

146
00:06:53,663 --> 00:06:57,291
- Okay then. Uh, stay here first.
- [indistinct chattering]

147
00:06:57,375 --> 00:07:00,628
- I'll just talk to your teacher, okay?
- [Ibyang] Okay.

148
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,672
[Cathy] Oh. [chuckles]

149
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:05,424
Hope we don't run out of chocolate.

150
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:07,426
It's really the kids' favorite.

151
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,887
[lively chattering]

152
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:12,807
- Oh, chocolate for him too!
- So, you're just here.

153
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:16,394
Don't you dare leave,
because I told my mommy about you!

154
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:19,814
I told on you too. You're in trouble.

155
00:07:20,314 --> 00:07:21,899
Ah, is that so?

156
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:23,860
Well then.

157
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:25,361
We're even.

158
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:26,821
[cackles]

159
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,990
You're really mean!

160
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:32,910
At least I'm loved by my mommy.

161
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:34,078
How about you?

162
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,998
Many people love me too!

163
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,499
[scoffs] Who?

164
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,127
Your dad, who's a fake like you?

165
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:44,422
Until you find your real parents, Ibyang,

166
00:07:44,505 --> 00:07:47,008
you're forever adopted. You're a loser!

167
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:48,050
[Janine shrieks]

168
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:49,969
[Ibyang] You thought
I won't fight back, huh?

169
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:52,138
You're the one who's ugly!

170
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,015
[both grunting]

171
00:07:54,098 --> 00:07:56,100
- All right, I'll go first.
- [Ibyang] You're the one who's ugly

172
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,310
because you have a bad attitude.

173
00:07:57,393 --> 00:07:59,770
- [grunting]
- [clamoring]

174
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:04,484
[children] There's a fight!
A fight! There's a fight!

175
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:06,736
[Atoy] Uh, ma'am.

176
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:08,237
Yes, sir? What is it?

177
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:11,574
I just want to raise a concern,

178
00:08:11,657 --> 00:08:15,119
about the bullying experienced by Ibyang.

179
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:17,163
- Ibyang? Who's bullying her?
- Hm-mm.

180
00:08:17,246 --> 00:08:18,748
You can talk to them,

181
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:21,626
but it's better if we also
talk to the parents.

182
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:25,129
Is it true a first grader
is bullying Janine?

183
00:08:25,213 --> 00:08:26,172
[in English] Yes.

184
00:08:26,797 --> 00:08:30,426
You're aware Janine
was once adopted, right?!

185
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,471
Her name is Janine, a grade two student.

186
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:37,350
Maybe it's better if I also
talk to the parents.

187
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:42,313
[teacher] I understand, especially
since Ibyang's situation is difficult,

188
00:08:42,855 --> 00:08:44,398
being adopted.

189
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:49,654
Yes, and we were also told
you are her real mother?

190
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:50,571
[in English] That's correct.

191
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:53,115
That's why it's important
to me to fix this,

192
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:55,952
because what that child is doing
to my daughter is wrong.

193
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:59,956
Yes. It's really not right that…

194
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:03,376
they hear things like that.
It's distressing for the child.

195
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:07,964
Of course, and we won't allow bullying
to continue in our school.

196
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:13,469
All right, maybe it's best if you bring me
to her parents, so we can fix this.

197
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:14,971
[teacher] Okay.

198
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,681
- [child] There's a fight!
- [grunting]

199
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:18,140
[child] There's a fight!

200
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:20,268
[clamoring]

201
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:23,271
- [child 1] There's a fight!
- [in English] Excuse me.

202
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,147
[clamoring]

203
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,107
[Audrey] Janine?

204
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:28,943
[Audrey] Dear!

205
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:31,862
- [grunts]
- [Atoy] Ibyang!

206
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:34,198
- [Audrey] Janine, my child!
- [Atoy] Stop that, stop that.

207
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:36,158
- [heavy breathing]
- [Atoy] Stop that.

208
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:38,786
[soft rock music playing]

209
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:42,873
She's your child?

210
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,878
So, you're the mother of Ibyang's bully.

211
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:51,757
Bully? She's the one bullying my child!

212
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:55,177
[somber music playing]

213
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,179
I thought you were kind.

214
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:59,307
That's not true!

215
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:01,726
She started all of this!

216
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:03,102
She's a liar, Mommy!

217
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:06,105
- She's always bullying me at school!
- Shush, dear.

218
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:07,481
She's the one I told you about,

219
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,400
always bullying me at school!

220
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:11,110
No, Mommy. No, she--

221
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:13,195
She's lying. She's lying!

222
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:16,324
[sobbing]

223
00:10:16,407 --> 00:10:17,366
[Audrey] Dear.

224
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:19,368
Wow!

225
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,162
[Janine sobbing]

226
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:22,997
Do you have something to say?

227
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,081
Nothing.

228
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:26,667
So, you have nothing to say.

229
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,545
Talk to Ibyang,
and let's go our separate ways.

230
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,840
I believe Ibyang.

231
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:34,675
She wouldn't tell a lie.

232
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:37,762
So, is that proof
that my child is really the bully?

233
00:10:37,845 --> 00:10:41,682
All I'm saying is we have two versions.

234
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:45,436
Next time, don't lecture me
about my child.

235
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:48,272
[in English] Let's go, Janine.

236
00:10:48,356 --> 00:10:51,776
[unsettling music playing]

237
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,695
[Atoy] Were you hurt?

238
00:10:57,573 --> 00:10:58,741
[music fades]

239
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,535
Do you think Atoy can help Ibyang?

240
00:11:01,619 --> 00:11:02,453
Of course.

241
00:11:03,037 --> 00:11:05,831
We all know Ibyang
was just waiting for him, right?

242
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:09,043
That's what I've been telling you.

243
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,586
I know Ibyang.

244
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:13,798
When she is promised something,
she will expect it.

245
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,132
Of course, she's a child.

246
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:19,720
Yes. I get you, Ame.
But it's not bad to make an effort, right?

247
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,639
Oh, of course.

248
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:23,307
Next time, just do better.

249
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:25,267
- Oh?
- [quirky sting]

250
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:27,353
Wow!

251
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,647
Why? Do you know magic?

252
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,315
Do you want me to show you?

253
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:32,608
Okay, show me.

254
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:33,776
[Karla] You know,

255
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,070
you two could really have something.

256
00:11:36,153 --> 00:11:37,863
- What kind of something?
- [Tonet] That's it.

257
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:39,031
There's something wrong already.

258
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:40,199
[chuckles]

259
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:42,701
No, your tandem is really good.

260
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,703
Emerson and Ame.

261
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,080
- "E-Me". Oh!
- [quirky sting]

262
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:47,248
[laughs]

263
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,499
They're "Eme", a joke!

264
00:11:48,582 --> 00:11:50,751
- [laughing]
- [pleasant music playing]

265
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:53,129
[Tonet] You two are a match.

266
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:54,296
You're annoying. Really.

267
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,423
Hey, Karla.

268
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:58,050
- Mmm?
- You invited Gavin…

269
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:00,428
I didn't invite him.

270
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:02,680
I just told him we were coming here too.

271
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:05,349
- Hey, how are you?
- [gentle music playing]

272
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:08,352
Cathy's here too. Did you know?

273
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:10,771
She has an outreach program here.
Cool, right?

274
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:13,315
Yes, cool!

275
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:15,776
So, she's doing outreach here too?

276
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:17,778
So, Karla?

277
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,280
Will you help me with Cathy?

278
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,323
[light music playing]

279
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:25,327
‪[inaudible]

280
00:12:26,036 --> 00:12:28,122
- We're heading home.
- [Tonet] Mm.

281
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:30,749
And I'm Ibyang's chaperone today.

282
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,835
Is that so?

283
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:35,921
All right, that's fine. I'll go ahead.

284
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:37,965
[Karla] Okay.

285
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:40,301
What's that?

286
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:43,262
Gavin still wants you
to be his bridge to his crush?

287
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:45,264
I already refused, didn't I?

288
00:12:45,347 --> 00:12:48,225
That's fine. That's not really
a thing anymore,

289
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:49,560
matchmaking like that.

290
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,438
Psst, hey.

291
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:55,065
What was that?

292
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,276
- [Tonet titters]
- Is that your boyfriend?

293
00:12:57,359 --> 00:12:58,903
- [Emerson] Huh?
- Not at all.

294
00:12:58,986 --> 00:13:00,112
[Emerson] No.

295
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:01,906
- [Emerson] So, he's your friend?
- Just a friend.

296
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,282
[Emerson] Oh, so just a friend.

297
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:06,660
He's your friend, but you refused when…

298
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,245
he needed you.

299
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:14,210
[music fades]

300
00:13:14,293 --> 00:13:16,629
Don't you believe me, Mommy?

301
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:19,006
Of course I believe you, dear.

302
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:20,883
[Janine] But it doesn't seem like it.

303
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,677
You didn't even scold Ibyang.

304
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:25,763
[in English] Janine, enough!

305
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,682
I already talked to her father, right?!

306
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,645
Who is that? Do you know him?

307
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:35,022
No, but…

308
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:38,192
Ibyang calls him "master".

309
00:13:38,275 --> 00:13:40,778
Not daddy or father.

310
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:42,238
Why master?

311
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,697
Who is he?

312
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,158
Who is he really?

313
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,993
[pensive music playing]

314
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:50,037
Your hair is soft, Mark.

315
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:51,664
Who's Mark?

316
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:53,916
Maybe that's your name.

317
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:57,336
If it's not not Mark,

318
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,338
maybe, Ryan?

319
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:00,923
[in English] Wait, wait.

320
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:08,347
You also look like…
Joshua. And wait, from this angle…

321
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,432
Enzo?

322
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:12,518
Enzo.

323
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:13,852
[chuckles] Enzo?

324
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:17,106
Those names sound like they grew up
with air-conditioning.

325
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:18,023
Ah, okay, okay.

326
00:14:18,107 --> 00:14:21,360
Then, Godofredo.

327
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:22,528
- Do you want that?
- Godofredo?

328
00:14:22,611 --> 00:14:23,904
Restituto?

329
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,240
- [scoffs]
- Ah, I know!

330
00:14:26,323 --> 00:14:28,450
- This is it. This is really it.
- [Atoy] What?

331
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:29,577
Dominador!

332
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:31,662
Those names sound like the names of D.O.M.

333
00:14:31,745 --> 00:14:32,746
[Audrey chuckles softly]

334
00:14:34,206 --> 00:14:35,666
[Atoy] You might be surprised.

335
00:14:37,376 --> 00:14:41,255
Maybe something like… Atoy.

336
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:46,010
Mommy, do you want to meet that man?

337
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,305
Ah, no, no. Um, you know…

338
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,225
Let's just forget them.

339
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:55,394
Didn't you invite me here?

340
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:58,647
This is our first-ever bonding
as mother and daughter.

341
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:04,153
Can we just… enjoy ourselves?

342
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:08,532
[gentle music playing]

343
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:16,707
Gavin, wait.

344
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:18,918
I'll help you with Cathy.

345
00:15:19,001 --> 00:15:19,960
Are you sure?

346
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,503
I mean, I told you it's okay if--

347
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:23,047
Yes! I already agreed, didn't I?

348
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,340
It's fine.

349
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:26,967
And we're friends.

350
00:15:27,051 --> 00:15:28,469
I don't leave people hanging.

351
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,555
[in English] I really
appreciate this, Karla.

352
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:35,643
I don't know.
I can't understand myself. It's like…

353
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:38,270
[in English] I'm not usually like this.

354
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:41,440
That's why I don't know why
I'm like this with Cathy.

355
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:44,234
It's like I'm so afraid to make
the first move with her. I don't know.

356
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:45,444
I get it.

357
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:46,987
I get you.

358
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:49,490
So, what's our play?

359
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:51,617
[mellow music playing]

360
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:54,161
I want to surprise her with flowers.

361
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,621
Do you know where I can buy some?

362
00:15:56,246 --> 00:15:58,248
I saw a shop outside. There's one.

363
00:15:58,832 --> 00:16:00,084
All right, let's go!

364
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,795
I'll just go to Cathy, and is it okay

365
00:16:02,878 --> 00:16:04,421
if you buy the flowers?

366
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:07,841
Something that would put
a smile on her face,

367
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:09,093
if you get that.

368
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:11,971
I trust your instincts.
So, it's up to you.

369
00:16:12,054 --> 00:16:14,723
Two thousand pesos, here.
This should be enough.

370
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:19,979
Thank you so much, Karla.
Thank you so much.

371
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:22,022
I'll go to her now, okay? I'll be back.

372
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:32,157
If that happens, call me, okay?

373
00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:36,829
Then, who was the first… Did she slap you?

374
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:38,163
- [Tonet] Oh!
- [murmurs]

375
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,249
- Atoy, Ibyang!
- You shout, okay?

376
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,001
Yoo-hoo! So, you're here.

377
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,962
I knew I'd find you here.

378
00:16:46,171 --> 00:16:47,214
Oh?

379
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:49,341
[in Visayan] Why are you sad, baby girl?

380
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,218
[Tonet] Are you still sad?

381
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:55,014
Well, because the bully is here.

382
00:16:55,097 --> 00:16:57,349
[in Visayan] Where is she?
I'm going to punch her!

383
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:58,767
I'll confront her!

384
00:16:58,851 --> 00:17:00,102
I'll curl her hair,

385
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:02,187
then shave her head, so she'll learn.

386
00:17:02,271 --> 00:17:03,647
[sneaky music playing]

387
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:07,443
Um, I'm not sad because of Janine.

388
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,696
I don't want to think about her.

389
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,699
I'm just sad because…

390
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:16,368
Mama Mary turned out to be her mother.

391
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:22,499
Too bad. I imagined she was my mother.

392
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,877
Who is this Mama Mary
Ibyang is talking about?

393
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:26,962
She met her at the park.

394
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,884
Master, why do you know Auntie Audrey?

395
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:34,303
Do you have a past?

396
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:36,263
- Huh?
- Past?

397
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:37,848
- What past are you talking about?
- [Ibyang] Oh.

398
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:40,309
- She was just my client.
- [Ibyang] Mmm…

399
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:41,560
Client?

400
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:45,064
So, you also found Janine?

401
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:47,649
I had nothing to do with that.

402
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:51,570
Ah, here's what we'll do.

403
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:52,946
I'll just go with you.

404
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:55,824
All right, I like that.

405
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:57,743
- Wait.
- [bright music playing]

406
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,204
By the way, the ice cream.

407
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:02,081
Stay here. I'll get ice cream.

408
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:03,040
Okay?

409
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:04,333
- Do you want some too?
- [Ibyang] Yes.

410
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,043
- Okay.
- Vanilla.

411
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:07,377
Uh-huh.

412
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:08,295
[titters]

413
00:18:08,378 --> 00:18:10,506
Oh, it's nice there.

414
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:14,134
[muffled chattering in the distance]

415
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:17,137
One chocolate, miss, in a cup.

416
00:18:20,224 --> 00:18:22,017
So, you're Ibyang's guardian.

417
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:24,686
And she calls you "master".

418
00:18:25,604 --> 00:18:27,356
So Master is your name?

419
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:29,191
[light music playing]

420
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:31,735
Do you think that's my birth name?

421
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:33,237
How would I know?

422
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:35,781
You never really introduced
yourself to me.

423
00:18:38,117 --> 00:18:38,992
Do I have to?

424
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,495
I didn't ask.

425
00:18:42,162 --> 00:18:43,872
Sir Atoy, any toppings?

426
00:18:43,956 --> 00:18:44,790
[Atoy] None.

427
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:47,167
So, it's just Atoy.

428
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:52,131
You act like your name is Sixto or Arturo.

429
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:54,675
Actually, it's Anthony.

430
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:56,718
[music fades]

431
00:18:58,178 --> 00:19:01,306
Where is… Ibyang's mother?

432
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:05,727
Can you just focus on your child?

433
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,604
[in English] Sorry.

434
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:09,314
[somber music playing]

435
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,524
Why?

436
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:13,694
So, where is Janine's father?

437
00:19:18,448 --> 00:19:20,075
Is she my daughter?

438
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:23,412
[sentimental music playing]

439
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:30,294
You're so assuming.

440
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:31,420
Why?

441
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:33,255
Think about it.

442
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,090
If my arithmetic is right, hasn't it been

443
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:39,678
eight years since we last
met on the island?

444
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:41,889
And Janine, how old is she?

445
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:44,975
[in English] Eight years old, grade two.

446
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:48,854
Doesn't that seem like something?

447
00:19:48,937 --> 00:19:52,316
In your arithmetic, didn't you consider

448
00:19:52,399 --> 00:19:54,359
I met someone else besides you?

449
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:57,321
Your confidence is something else, huh?

450
00:19:57,905 --> 00:19:58,739
Why?

451
00:19:59,239 --> 00:20:01,575
Was I the only one you had
a relationship with back then?

452
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:03,076
[suspicious music playing]

453
00:20:10,334 --> 00:20:12,169
[music fades]

454
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:16,131
[in English] Oh, it's you.

455
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:17,549
[in English] Hi, Cathy.

456
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:18,467
[in English] Hi.

457
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,345
I saw the kids you were
taking care of earlier.

458
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:24,932
They're so cute, right?

459
00:20:25,849 --> 00:20:27,226
Uh, you?

460
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,186
Why are you here?

461
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:32,189
I just joined my cousin's field trip.

462
00:20:34,816 --> 00:20:35,901
Okay.

463
00:20:36,902 --> 00:20:39,571
All right then. I'll go ahead.

464
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:41,406
Wait, wait!

465
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:44,493
[light music playing]

466
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,622
Do you see that? There, look.

467
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:51,291
- Gavin, where? I really can't see.
- [indistinct]

468
00:20:52,709 --> 00:20:54,962
- There! It's beautiful, right?
- Where?

469
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:56,713
There, so beautiful.

470
00:20:56,797 --> 00:20:58,548
What is it really?

471
00:20:58,632 --> 00:21:00,050
There, look! At the very top, look.

472
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:04,221
Oh, Gavin, what is it--

473
00:21:06,306 --> 00:21:07,182
[chuckles]

474
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:08,725
Is that for me?

475
00:21:09,309 --> 00:21:10,894
[in English] Of course, Cathy.

476
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:11,937
[in English] Hope you like it.

477
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,277
You're so corny.

478
00:21:18,902 --> 00:21:20,946
You kept pointing somewhere!

479
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:22,531
[Gavin] At least I made you smile.

480
00:21:24,074 --> 00:21:26,326
[music fades]

481
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,327
[buzzing]

482
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:28,370
- [squeals]
- [Gavin] Oh!

483
00:21:28,453 --> 00:21:29,913
- [buzzing]
- [playful music playing]

484
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:33,417
[Cathy squealing]

485
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,501
Karla, what do we do?

486
00:21:34,584 --> 00:21:35,419
I don't know, Gavin!

487
00:21:35,502 --> 00:21:37,337
- I don't take care of bees!
- [Gavin] Cathy!

488
00:21:38,422 --> 00:21:40,340
Mmm, it went like that.

489
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:41,758
[Tonet mutters]

490
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:42,676
- Wow!
- [shrieks]

491
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,803
[Ibyang] Thanks, Master!

492
00:21:44,886 --> 00:21:46,972
- You're something else, Atoy.
- Mmm.

493
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:48,432
- Are you okay?
- Delicious.

494
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:50,517
Of course. Thank you, Tonet.

495
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:54,438
- Master.
- Mmm?

496
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:58,191
After this, can we go on rides?

497
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:00,902
Of course. Why else would I rush here?

498
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:04,281
So you better finish
that ice cream quickly,

499
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:06,575
so we can go on the rides
with big bro Atoy.

500
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:08,577
Hey, Tonet, you don't have to do this.

501
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:09,828
- If you want to walk--
- Shh.

502
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:13,373
I want to do this.
I'll join you and Ibyang.

503
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:14,750
[light music playing]

504
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:15,876
Let's go.

505
00:22:16,501 --> 00:22:17,586
‪[indistinct chattering]

506
00:22:24,634 --> 00:22:26,470
[sneaky music playing]

507
00:22:26,553 --> 00:22:28,346
Thread through the needle.

508
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:31,475
Negativity will just pass.

509
00:22:32,059 --> 00:22:33,435
Negativity will just pass.

510
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:41,318
Is that the mother of the bully?

511
00:22:43,195 --> 00:22:44,654
[music fades]

512
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:45,572
‪[dramatic stinging]

513
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:52,913
[mellow music playing]

514
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:00,378
In fairness.

515
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:01,296
[sharp inhale]

516
00:23:01,379 --> 00:23:02,422
[in Visayan] She does look like Mama Mary.

517
00:23:03,256 --> 00:23:05,801
[sneaky music playing]

518
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:18,105
We're next.

519
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:20,065
You can do it.

520
00:23:20,899 --> 00:23:24,361
[exclaiming and squealing]

521
00:23:24,444 --> 00:23:25,737
I really don't want to!

522
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,031
[exclaiming and squealing]

523
00:23:28,115 --> 00:23:30,450
[light music playing]

524
00:23:31,159 --> 00:23:32,160
‪[screaming]

525
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:42,462
- [buzzing]
- [grunts]

526
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:44,422
Cathy! Cathy!

527
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:48,593
- [buzzing]
- [grunting, gasping, shrieks]

528
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:49,928
[Gavin] Cathy!

529
00:23:52,722 --> 00:23:54,933
What did you do?!
Why did you push me into the water?!

530
00:23:55,016 --> 00:23:56,977
[Karla] So you wouldn't
get stung by the bees!

531
00:23:57,060 --> 00:23:57,978
Come on! Hold on to me!

532
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:59,312
[Gavin] Careful, careful, careful!

533
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:01,982
- Are you okay?
- [Cathy sighs]

534
00:24:03,191 --> 00:24:05,694
- You?!
- [in English] You guys know each other?

535
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:07,654
She's the one who stole our basketball.

536
00:24:07,737 --> 00:24:09,948
Oh, what?! I didn't steal that!

537
00:24:10,031 --> 00:24:12,367
That was payment for the damage
you did to my car!

538
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:13,410
[sneaky music playing]

539
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:15,662
Gavin, do you know her?!

540
00:24:15,745 --> 00:24:17,122
[in English] She's my friend, Karla!

541
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:19,207
She helped me buy flowers for you.

542
00:24:19,291 --> 00:24:21,585
[in English] Oh, I see!

543
00:24:21,668 --> 00:24:23,879
You accused me
of stealing your basketball.

544
00:24:23,962 --> 00:24:26,798
So, you put a bee there to get back at me.

545
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:27,716
[in English] Congrats, huh!

546
00:24:27,799 --> 00:24:29,342
And you, are you thinking straight?!

547
00:24:29,426 --> 00:24:32,095
Do you think I can put a bee in a flower?!

548
00:24:32,179 --> 00:24:34,264
What am I, a bee whisperer?!

549
00:24:34,347 --> 00:24:35,515
Why don't you just admit it?!

550
00:24:37,184 --> 00:24:39,519
[unsettling music playing]

551
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:40,687
[exclaims in frustration]

552
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:42,522
Cathy!

553
00:24:44,566 --> 00:24:46,067
[music fades]

554
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,986
[vendor] Oh, just one gondola left!

555
00:24:48,069 --> 00:24:49,112
[Janine gasps]

556
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:50,071
Ah, ah--

557
00:24:50,155 --> 00:24:52,199
[stutters] Mommy, we were first.

558
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:55,327
We were ahead by a few steps!

559
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,078
[sneaky music playing]

560
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:58,455
Uh, fine.

561
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:00,165
Let them go first.

562
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,302
[music fades]

563
00:25:12,385 --> 00:25:13,637
[playful music playing]

564
00:25:21,519 --> 00:25:23,605
[electronic blipping]

565
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:24,522
‪[tense music playing]

566
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:32,948
[Tonet] <i>This is a sure shot, Ibyang.</i>

567
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:34,032
Look, Ibyang.

568
00:25:34,115 --> 00:25:34,908
[clicks, then thuds]

569
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:36,326
Ibyang.

570
00:25:36,409 --> 00:25:38,078
- [Ibyang shrieks]
- [Tonet] Wow! [exclaims]

571
00:25:38,161 --> 00:25:41,498
- Mommy, I want that too!
- Hello!

572
00:25:41,581 --> 00:25:44,376
Aren't you the mother of Ibyang's bully?

573
00:25:44,459 --> 00:25:46,836
[Tonet] <i>Sorry.</i>
<i>Are you stalking me and Atoy?</i>

574
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:52,092
Master, you'll both attend
the pageant, right?

575
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:53,843
We'll both be there.

576
00:25:53,927 --> 00:25:55,971
That's why we became
your guardians, right?

577
00:25:56,054 --> 00:25:57,430
[Mercado on the phone] <i>How are you, Atoy?</i>

578
00:25:57,514 --> 00:25:59,975
I have an old VIP client.

579
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:02,852
I said you can start right away.

580
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:04,437
Tomorrow?

581
00:26:04,521 --> 00:26:05,313
UP NEXT

582
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,815
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

583
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:08,984
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

584
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:11,403
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i>
<i>In the tangle</i> ♪

585
00:26:11,486 --> 00:26:14,030
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
